<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3186] nodetool should not NPE when rack/dc info is not yet available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3186</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As the title says.  What happens is the persisted ring is loaded, but if those nodes are down and you&apos;re using a snitch like ec2 that gets rack/dc info from gossip, nodetool NPEs instead of showing that the node is down.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12522798">CASSANDRA-3186</key>
